<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Champion Wrestler was a 2D wrestling arcade machine game released in 1989 by Taito in which players can select from ten different wrestlers, including such Taito game luminaries as Miracle Rastan. Each wrestler is rated for several attributes: power, durability, speed, technique and resilience. The wrestlers also have several signature moves, in addition to some common wrestling techniques like the body slam and the suplex.
                  <br><br>Some of the wrestlers also have managers who stand at ringside and occasionally throw weapons into the ring. Most matches are of the regular variety and can be won through a straight pin or by forcing the opponent out of the ring and then having him counted out. Every so often though, players will have to engage in cage matches. During these matches, wrestlers cannot be thrown out of the ring, but can be thrown against the cage for damage.
                  <br><br>Champion Wrestler - Jikkyou Live is the Playstation version of the classic arcade machine wqith different game modes:
                  <br>- Career: Choose a wrestler and try to win the TWF Championship. Not avaliable at the beginning of the game.
                  <br>- Single: Choose a wrestler and play against computer opponents in tag, battle royal or single modes.
                  <br>- Vs: Play against the computer or another human player.
                  <br>- Training: Train with the computer or another human player.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Wrestling game "champion wrestler," which gained popularity in the arcade, was reborn in addition to the immersive live by Shigeru Kajihara! Up to four people can play simultaneously as well, you can also enjoy a large number of people tag match incandescent. In order to take the TWF championship belt, the game will challenge us formidable enemy skills with.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>3D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Wrestling theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

